<br>
I went up because I was asked over guild chat to help out someone raiding PoF. I head to Ferrott and find out a bunch of people have had rez timers go bye-bye. Well I'm thinking it isn't a good idea to go up, but I said I would and I honor my commitments. About 10 people came as reinforcements. I zone in, get to the north camp, and then someone trains the camp with 2 shivers and 2 scarelings. I die. Whatever.<br>
<br>
Get rezzed pretty quickly. Find out there is a total of 1 cleric in PoF at the time and he has to leave soon. Supposedly another cleric is going to come. Well the cleric in the plane has stayed much longer than he commited to, and there are still a bunch of corpses around the zone, and no other cleric to rez. People start gating out at this point leaving about 18 of us up there. I was willing to camp out and wait for another day and someone to clear the plane, but 2 of my guildmates had gone up as reinforcements and their corpses were still sitting in the plane. So I sit and wait.<br>
<br>
Through the use of zone in and die while Necro summons your corpse they get the cleric's corpse to camp and rezzed. Eventually they use this method for my guildmates. As soon as they get rezzed it seems someone wandered off the hill and 2 nightmares aggro'ed on the camp. Bam everyone rezzed dies including the cleric.<br>
<br>
Now it gets to a point where the only rezzer in the plane is Necreia, a paly with ghetto rez. Well the cleric up there refuses to take the rez since it isn't his character and he doesn't want to penalize the person with a non-exp rez. I'd call that selfish to the others who died up in the plane, but selfish is probably an understatement.<br>
<br>
I personally don't care about exp and I wanted to get my guildmates out of there and offered to do anything to get them up and rezzed, including training the portal and clearing a path for others. Eventually someone who had a cleric (Drakuul?) camped up there was kind enough to log in and rez me and my fallen guildmates and we got out of dodge.<br>
<br>
While I was up there for over 2 hours, not once did it appear that their was an actual raid leader. I checked the calendar with my second comp while I was up there and it was supposed to be a Xerxis raid. I have no problem with fubar situations, but no one took charge or responsibility while up there. And it is sad when all the tp'ers get rezzed and tp out leaving tanks up there.<br>
<br>
I mainly ask the next time someone invites people on a raid they inform them that there are basically no clerics on the raid and that it is solely a CR mission and not an actual plane raid. Asking people to come to a plane raid when it is a death trap is extremely unfair.<br>
<br>
A big thanks to Tiluvar who bound up there and tp'ed me out. I hope the loop deaths didn't take too much experience.<br>
